// ============================================================
// SetupScript.gs — BLC Nexus Setup
// src/setup/SetupScript.gs
//
// PURPOSE: One-time (and re-runnable) setup script that creates
// all required sheet tabs with correct headers and seeds
// essential reference data.
//
// HOW TO RUN:
//   1. Open BLC_Nexus_DEV_Core in Google Sheets
//   2. Extensions → Apps Script
//   3. Select function: runSetup
//   4. Click Run
//
// INDIVIDUAL FUNCTIONS (run from Apps Script editor):
//   runSetup()         — full setup (schemas + seed data + version)
//   runSetupSchemas()  — create / verify sheet tabs and headers only
//   runSetupSeedData() — insert seed rows only (safe to re-run)
//   runVerify()        — check all expected tabs exist, log results
//
// IDEMPOTENCY:
//   All operations check before acting:
//   - Tabs: created only if they don't exist
//   - Headers: written only to empty sheets (row count = 0)
//   - Seed rows: inserted only if not already present
//   Safe to run against a live sheet without data loss.
//
// NOTE ON SpreadsheetApp:
//   This file calls SpreadsheetApp directly — the only file
//   besides DAL.gs with this permission. SetupScript bootstraps
//   the infrastructure that DAL depends on. Once setup is
//   complete, all other modules use DAL exclusively.
//
// FIRST-RUN CHECKLIST (run in this order):
//   1. Set Config.gs SPREADSHEET_IDS.DEV to the real spreadsheet ID
//   2. Run runSetup() from the Apps Script editor
//   3. Verify with runVerify() — all tabs should show ✅
//   4. Add real staff to DIM_STAFF_ROSTER
//   5. Add real clients to DIM_CLIENT_MASTER
//   6. Add real product rates to DIM_PRODUCT_RATES
//   7. Set up triggers via Triggers.gs (next step)
// ============================================================

// ============================================================
// SCHEMA DEFINITIONS
//
// Maps every table name → its header row array.
// This is the single source of truth for column names.
// If you add a column, add it here and re-run runSetupSchemas().
//
// Column order matters — DAL maps by header name, not position,
// but keeping a consistent order aids manual sheet inspection.
// ============================================================

